# BaseAnchor

BaseAnchor is the low-level anchored popover for TuffEx: Floating UI owns placement, collision handling, arrow positioning, and reference tracking; GSAP owns enter/leave motion.

Panels use `TxCard` by default; control appearance via `panelBackground / panelShadow / panelRadius / panelPadding`. Set `useCard=false` when you only need a raw wrapper.

## Basic Usage

### BaseAnchor
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor v-model="open" placement="bottom-start">
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton>Click</TxButton>
      </template>

      <div style="width: 220px; padding: 4px;">
        Popover content with anchor-positioned motion.
      </div>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## Transfer Motion

`animation.type='transfer'` is the default motion: content enters from the placement direction through a soft edge and returns through the same direction on close. Pair with `show-arrow` to render a triangle that follows final floating placement and offset.

### Soft Edge
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorSplitLineDemo" code-lang="vue"}
