## Animation Modes

Use one `animation` object to configure motion. Supported modes: `transfer` (default directional reveal), `boom` (focus-scale with blur, scale, and opacity), `opacity` (fade only), and `none` (instant show/hide).

### Multiple Animations
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorAnimationDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor
      v-model="open"
      placement="bottom"
      :show-arrow="true"
      :animation="{ type: 'boom', duration: 420, scale: 1.08, blur: 14 }"
    >
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton>Focus Scale</TxButton>
      </template>

      <div style="width: 220px; padding: 4px;">
        Anchor-positioned motion with blur, scale, and opacity.
      </div>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

## Custom Animation

Prefer the `animation` object for type, duration, and GSAP easing. `duration` / `ease` remain as compatibility fallbacks.

### Custom Ease
:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="BaseAnchorCustomEaseDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <script setup lang="ts">
  import { ref } from 'vue'

  const open = ref(false)
  </script>

  <template>
    <TxBaseAnchor
      v-model="open"
      placement="bottom-start"
      :animation="{ type: 'transfer', duration: 600, ease: 'elastic.out(1, 0.4)' }"
    >
      <template #reference>
        <TxButton>Elastic</TxButton>
      </template>

      <div style="width: 240px; padding: 4px;">
        Elastic easing with 600ms duration.
      </div>
    </TxBaseAnchor>
  </template>
---
:::

